Place a #baking sheet{} on top rack of #oven{} and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash
and dry all produce. Halve, deseed, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved,
deseeded, and thinly sliced). Peel and thinly slice @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly
sliced into rounds). Roughly chop @garlic{2%cloves}(roughly chopped). Roughly chop
@black olives{1%oz}(roughly chopped). Tear @fresh mozzarella{4%oz}(torn into small
pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add
@Italian seasoning{1%tsp} and half the garlic. Cook until fragrant, about
~{1%minute}. Add @tomato paste{3%tbsp}, 1/4 cup water, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Bring
to a simmer, then turn off heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #cutting board{}. Rub each side with a drizzle of oil.
Using a #spoon{}, evenly spread flatbreads with tomato sauce. Top with bell pepper
and as much shallot and olives as you like. Evenly top with mozzarella.

Transfer assembled flatbreads to preheated baking sheet. Bake on top rack until
flatbreads are browned and crisp and cheese has melted, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine remaining garlic, a pinch of
@chili flakes{1%tsp}, and @butter{3%tbsp}. Microwave on high until melted and
fragrant, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{}.

Transfer baked flatbreads to a cutting board; cut into wedges. Serve with chili
garlic butter for drizzling on top and dipping crusts into.